<p>Akkadian was also a source of borrowing to other languages, above all <a href="/wiki/Sumerian_language" title="Sumerian language">Sumerian</a>. Some examples are: Sumerian <i>da-ri</i> ('lastingly', from Akkadian <i>dƒÅru</i>), Sumerian <i>ra gaba</i> ('riders, messenger', from Akkadian <i>rƒÅkibu</i>).
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Sample_text">Sample text</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Akkadian_language&amp;action=edit&amp;section=37" title="Edit section: Sample text">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<p>The following is the 7th section of the <a href="/wiki/Code_of_Hammurabi" title="Code of Hammurabi">Hammurabi law code</a>, written in the mid-18th century BC:
</p>
<div class="interlinear"><div style="float: left; margin-bottom: 0.3em;margin-right: 1em;"><p lang="akk" style="margin: 0px;font-style: italic;">≈°umma</p><p style="margin: 0px;">if</p></div><div style="float: left; margin-bottom: 0.3em;margin-right: 1em;"><p lang="akk" style="margin: 0px;font-style: italic;">awƒ´l-um</p><p style="margin: 0px;">man-<abbr class="gloss-abbr" title="nominative case" style="font-variant: small-caps; font-variant-numeric: oldstyle-nums; text-transform: lowercase;"><a href="/wiki/Nominative_case" title="Nominative case">NOM</a></abbr></p></div><div style="float: left; margin-bottom: 0.3em;margin-right: 1em;"><p lang="akk" style="margin: 0px;font-style: italic;">l≈´</p><p style="margin: 0px;">or</p></div><div style="float: left; margin-bottom: 0.3em;margin-right: 1em;"><p lang="akk" style="margin: 0px;font-style: italic;">kasp-am</p><p style="margin: 0px;">silver-<abbr class="gloss-abbr" title="accusative case" style="font-variant: small-caps; font-variant-numeric: oldstyle-nums; text-transform: lowercase;"><a href="/wiki/Accusative_case" title="Accusative case">ACC</a></abbr></p></div><div style="float: left; margin-bottom: 0.3em;margin-right: 1em;"><p lang="akk" style="margin: 0px;font-style: italic;">l≈´</p><p style="margin: 0px;">or</p></div><div style="float: left; margin-bottom: 0.3em;margin-right: 1em;"><p lang="akk" style="margin: 0px;font-style: italic;">·∏´urƒÅ·π£-am</p><p style="margin: 0px;">gold-<abbr class="gloss-abbr" title="accusative case" style="font-variant: small-caps; font-variant-numeric: oldstyle-nums; text-transform: lowercase;"><a href="/wiki/Accusative_case" title="Accusative case">ACC</a></abbr></p></div><div style="float: left; margin-bottom: 0.3em;margin-right: 1em;"><p lang="akk" style="margin: 0px;font-style: italic;">l≈´</p><p style="margin: 0px;">or</p></div><div style="float: left; margin-bottom: 0.3em;margin-right: 1em;"><p lang="akk" style="margin: 0px;font-style: italic;">ward-am</p><p style="margin: 0p